\‘You are the glass which mirrors my reflection;
Your name have I inscribed with mine together.’

God said moreover： ‘Well I know, my Prophet,
That gazing thus your soul will ne’er feel surfeit;

But go, and give my slaves my invitation
To come and gaze at will upon my features.’
